snippet.title: Science Behind Weatherproof Lenses #shorts #camera
snippet.description:
How do camera lenses stay clean during heavy rain? Some professional lenses have a centrifugal force-based cleaning system. The lens rotates at high speeds, causing water, snow, and mud to bounce right off. This technology ensures an unobstructed view, especially when recording in extreme weather.

snippet.title: Science Behind Weatherproof Lenses
snippet.description:
Science Behind Weatherproof Lenses
How do camera lenses stay clear in heavy rain? Some pro lenses use a cleaning system based on centrifugal force. The lens spins rapidly, making water, snow, and mud fly off instantly. This keeps the view sharp and clear, even when filming in extreme weather.
